' PlantUML example — Implementation layer: object lifecycle of a single
' data-subject-request (DSR) record in the DPO's DSR register.
'
' Derived from:
'   - canon/views/bpmn/data-subject-erasure.bpmn.transitrix.yaml
'       SE-REQUEST, TASK-VERIFY-IDENTITY, GW-VERIFIED, TASK-REJECT,
'       TASK-LOG-REQUEST, GW-ARCHIVE, TASK-FLAG-GAP, TASK-CONFIRM,
'       TASK-RECORD-CLOSURE, EE-CLOSED.
'   - canon/elements/02_business/processes/PROCESS-DSR-HANDLE-1.yaml
'       "fulfil data-subject rights requests ... within the GDPR statutory window."
'
' Not a duplicate of canon/views/state/order-lifecycle.state.md: that Mermaid
' view is the Order entity's lifecycle. This is a different entity (the DSR
' record itself) — object-state detail the BPMN task flow doesn't expose
' directly, same complementary pattern as the order-lifecycle view uses
' relative to PROCESS-ORD-FULFILL-1.

!include transitrix-theme.puml
@startuml DSR record — state model

[*] --> Received : erasure request received (SE-REQUEST)
Received --> IdentityCheck : verify data-subject identity (TASK-VERIFY-IDENTITY)
IdentityCheck --> Rejected : not verified (GW-VERIFIED, default)
IdentityCheck --> Logged : verified (TASK-LOG-REQUEST)
Rejected --> [*]

Logged --> Locating : locate personal data (TASK-LOCATE)
Locating --> Erasing : erase from active systems (TASK-ERASE-ACTIVE)
Erasing --> ArchiveException : data in cold-storage archive (GW-ARCHIVE)
Erasing --> Confirmed : no archive exposure (GW-ARCHIVE, default)
ArchiveException --> Confirmed : exception flagged (TASK-FLAG-GAP)

Confirmed --> Closed : record completion within 30-day window (TASK-RECORD-CLOSURE)
Closed --> [*]

@enduml
